"target":"Author/Yunmi Lee","line":76},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/mun_total_2017/mun_total_2017.pdf","line":78}],"metadata":{"id":"mun_total_2017","type":"article-journal","title":"Total Synthesis of Isohericerin, Isohericenone, and Erinacerin A: Development of a Copper-Catalyzed Methylboronation of Terminal Alkynes","issued":{"date-parts":[[2017]]},"DOI":"10.1021/acs.joc.7b00920","container-title":"Journal of Organic Chemistry","abstract":"Efficient and concise approaches for the synthesis of three bioactive natural products, isohericerin, isohericenone, and erinacerin A, are described in this paper. The key reactions employed include a Mannich reaction with commercially available hydroxybenzoate and subsequent one-pot lactamization to afford the common precursor isoindolinone in 3 steps and a Suzuki–Miyaura coupling reaction to connect geranyl side chains to the isoindolinone core. In addition, the mild and efficient synthesis of the C5′-oxidized geranyl side unit of isohericenone is enabled by developing a highly regioselective and efficient method for the Cu-catalyzed methylboronation of functionalized terminal alkynes.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Mun","given":"Bohyun","literal":""},{"family":"Mun","given":"Bohyun","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Sang Yong","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Sangyong","literal":""},{"family":"Yoon","given":"Hongju","literal":""},{"family":"Yoon","given":"Hongju","literal":""},{"family":"Yoon","given":"Hongju","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Ki-Hyun","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Ki Hyun","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Ki-Hyun","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Ki Hyun","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Yunmi","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Yunmi","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Yunmi","literal":""}],"citation-key":"mun_total_2017","year":"2017","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Total Synthesis of Isohericerin, Isohericenone, and Erinacerin A: Development of a Copper-Catalyzed Methylboronation of Terminal Alkynes"],"author-links":["[[Author/Bohyun Mun]]","[[Author/Bohyun Mun]]","[[Author/Sang Yong Kim]]","[[Author/Sangyong Kim]]","[[Author/Hongju Yoon]]","[[Author/Hongju Yoon]]","[[Author/Hongju Yoon]]","[[Author/Ki-Hyun Kim]]","[[Author/Ki Hyun Kim]]","[[Author/Ki-Hyun Kim]]","[[Author/Ki Hyun Kim]]","[[Author/Yunmi Lee]]","[[Author/Yunmi Lee]]","[[Author/Yunmi Lee]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/mun_total_2017/mun_total_2017.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1jc3wq9","at":1774951887563}},"smart_blocks:Research/@mun_total_2017.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.06049584,-0.01215786,-0.00225077,-0.00385633,0.00690866,-0.03242329,-0.04671984,0.00887372,-0.04223073,0.04095031,-0.00209368,-0.04525148,0.06140428,0.01296881,0.06416314,0.01122612,0.00081028,0.05682882,-0.06777796,-0.00257659,0.02917604,-0.07063154,0.03312353,-0.00412866,0.13280433,0.02243228,0.00417648,-0.00077116,-0.0468153,-0.26061049,-0.02972236,0.03569249,0.01331128,-0.04012672,0.0213373,-0.05625082,-0.02891355,0.01340043,0.02132984,-0.01534021,0.04606881,0.01817044,0.01579206,-0.01568807,0.04817022,-0.02182709,-0.0369662,0.00784763,0.005774,-0.06979056,0.01303161,-0.00241218,-0.04891955,0.02011282,0.06592166,0.08787889,0.02259197,0.00060614,0.02498403,-0.01445789,0.02074509,0.06551822,-0.20374888,0.03709618,0.04029991,-0.02554293,-0.02926076,-0.08112604,0.06772302,0.06442594,-0.02910957,-0.02648436,0.03656367,0.02905713,0.00721302,-0.00625161,0.03367146,-0.02466881,-0.04012808,-0.04159528,-0.00807948,0.06157329,-0.00467253,-0.00035295,-0.00568778,0.00279102,0.03746868,-0.01727635,0.04781298,0.0028164,-0.02154688,-0.06487743,-0.00080515,-0.03312967,-0.03855733,0.0388016,-0.00010441,-0.01772208,-0.03686037,0.09160823,-0.02527673,0.01734572,-0.03869633,-0.08087202,0.02498632,0.03165794,-0.01321054,-0.0